# SaaS Factory Cursor Rules

## Code Standards

- **Language**: TypeScript 5.0+ (strict mode)
- **Framework**: React 19 (app router)
- **Backend**: Node.js 20 LTS + Express/Fastify
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 15+
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4

## File Naming

- Components: PascalCase (Button.tsx)
- Utilities: camelCase (formatDate.ts)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (API_BASE_URL)
- Types: PascalCase + .ts extension (UserType.ts)

## Commit Messages

Format: `[AGENT:type] brief description`

Examples:
- `[AGENT:builder] feat: Add user authentication`
- `[AGENT:payments] fix: Fix Stripe webhook signature`
- `[AUDIT] chore: Update security audit report`

## Testing Requirements

- Unit tests: ≥ 80% coverage
- Integration tests: Critical paths
- E2E tests: User stories
- Load tests: 100+ concurrent users

## Security Checklist

- [ ] No secrets in code (use .env)
- [ ] HTTPS only (443)
- [ ] SQL injection protections (parameterized queries)
- [ ] CORS properly configured
- [ ] Rate limiting enabled
- [ ] Input validation on all forms

## Documentation

- Every public API must have JSDoc
- Complex logic needs inline comments
- Architecture decisions go to `knowledge/decisions.md`
- User-facing features need ADR

